cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a machine learning approach using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) to infer transportation modes from GPS trajectories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since CNNs are commonly used in these fields. The paper also involves data preprocessing and feature engineering, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
